                <head>58. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On March 5 at Ankara, representatives of the Governments of the United States,
                    Iran, and Pakistan signed identical bilateral agreements for cooperation in
                    promoting the security and defense of the members of the Baghdad Pact. For text
                    of the agreements, see <hi rend="italic">American Foreign Policy: Current
                        Documents, 1959</hi>, pages 1020–1023. See also <ref target="#d268">Document
                        268</ref>.</p>
            </div>
